      "updated": 1777638815655,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Basic GenAI based application as It is using LLM(s)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Basic GenAI based application as It is using LLM(s)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Gb-Yg5lfYBbME1Q302J8Q",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 272.828125,
      "y": 407.796875,
      "width": 1188.2978515625,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aD",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 981888226,
      "version": 1901,
      "versionNonce": 1376527614,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777640012306,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "But any LLM to build it has to go through multiple hops\n1. Pre-Training - where model is ingested with all of the data present on the internet\n2. Instruction based Post-Training - here sepecific information (Q/A) is ingested to train the model to train it to be\nable to chat\n3. Fine-Tuning - (Optional) - can be done on pre-trained models or post-trained models. Acually done to train the model\non specific domain, and update the parameters to be able to predict information about the domain.\n\nBut there is one drawback that the LLM has, that is it has a training cut off date:\n- This leads to data not being real-time, the current information is not present with the model\n\nFor example: Model cannot answer \"What is the current weather in Chicago?\" as it does not have the current information.\n\nThe solution is to augment the model with some external tools such as, web search, calculator, APIs that enhances the \ncapabilities of the model, by giving the model with real time context. This augmentation of tools on top of LLMs is called\nAgentic AI.\n\nHere is the ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "But any LLM to build it has to go through multiple hops\n1. Pre-Training - where model is ingested with all of the data present on the internet\n2. Instruction based Post-Training - here sepecific information (Q/A) is ingested to train the model to train it to be able to chat\n3. Fine-Tuning - (Optional) - can be done on pre-trained models or post-trained models. Acually done to train the model on specific domain, and update the parameters to be able to predict information about the domain.\n\nBut there is one drawback that the LLM has, that is it has a training cut off date:\n- This leads to data not being real-time, the current information is not present with the model\n\nFor example: Model cannot answer \"What is the current weather in Chicago?\" as it does not have the current information.\n\nThe solution is to augment the model with some external tools such as, web search, calculator, APIs that enhances the \ncapabilities of the model, by giving the model with real time context. This augmentation of tools on top of LLMs is called Agentic AI.\n\nHere is the ",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
